pr_review_comment_body:
We recently changed the format of the ``.send`` function so that it doesn't take a boolean as the last argument, but an ``options`` object.  So this should be changed to:

    thNotify.send(thPinboardCountError, 'danger', { sticky: true });

Sorry I didn't catch this the first time around.  And I realize this was old code that we'd somehow missed in the syntax change.  But let's fix it here anyway.  Thanks!  :)

these router calls can be tightened up a bit, e.g:

```javascript
        router.go({
          name: constants.PageNames.LEARN_CHANNEL,
          params: { channel_id: currentChannel },
        });
```

Per my understanding of the code and testing locally, the new result is:
```
server {
  server_name example.org;
  listen 80; # notice default_server is removed
  redirect http->https;
}
server {
  server_name example.org;
  listen 443 ssl; 
  # rest of the ssl directives
}
```
I'm not talking about `default_server` on the 443 `listen` statement. Instead, I'm talking about the one for port 80. Now the default server for port 80 is whichever one nginx parses first because it's not specified explicitly. It may be the same block, but it certainly may not. This is a change in behavior.

